@node MAIN "configuring.html"
     The Preferences program     Configuring Tag-o-Miga  

There are two ways to configure Tag-o-Miga - manually or automatically.  

Currently, automatic configuration is only available on the Amiga version. This is supplied with a program called Tag-o-Miga-Prefs. Information on how to use the program is available @{" " link "PREFERENCES.GUIDE/MAIN"} here.  

Manual configuration involves loading the configuration file into your text editor and changing the options by hand. The name of the configuration file varies depending on your platform - for DOS and Windows, it is a file called TAGOMIGA.CFG placed in the same directory as the Tag-o-Miga program. For Unix, it is a file called .tagomigarc placed in your home directory (or, more specifically, the directory referenced by $HOME). Manual configuration on the Amiga uses its environment system and manual configuration is not recommended.  

Click @{" " link "CONFIGFILE.GUIDE/MAIN"} here for information on the format of the configuration file.  
